@article{10.1145/2638555,
    abstract = {Sequential components are crucial for a real-time 
embedded system as they control the system based on the system's 
current state and real life input. In this article, we explore the 
security and trust issues of sequential system design from the 
perspective of a finite state machine (FSM), which is the most popular 
model used to describe sequential systems. Specifically, we find that 
the traditional FSM synthesis procedure will introduce security risks 
