Second, we analyze the status quo of the Web-based malware problem. 
Third, three categories of defense mechanisms are discussed in detail: 
(1) building honeypots with virtual machines or signature-based 
detection system to discover existing threats; (2) using code analysis 
and testing techniques to identify the vulnerabilities of Web 
applications; and (3) constructing reputation-based blacklists or 
smart sandbox systems to protect end-users from attacks. We show that 
