@article{10.1145/3288758,
    abstract = {Cache attacks allow attackers to infer the properties 
of a secret execution by observing cache hits and misses. But how much 
information can actually leak through such attacks? For a given 
program, a cache model, and an input, our CHALICE framework leverages 
